stanley n cohen lab lab information stan cohen's lab is located in the department of genetics at the stanford university school of medicine stan's primary field of research is molecular genetics and the research interests of his lab focus on understanding important biological processes and events at the molecular level his lab also develops bioinformatics tools to aid in this understanding research in the cohen lab is multifaceted rather than studying a particular organism stan tries to choose systems best suited to answering the particular questions that he and members of his lab group are interested in there are about 15 members of the cohen research group our investigations are supported by the nih dtra and the national foundation for cancer research 2002 2010 stanford university last updated december 4 2008
